**REMINDER: dont forget how to properly cite different types of texts. For the purpose of this class we will use MLA but Chicago is widely used in historical writing and APA is used in scientific literature.


CITATION examples:

An 1861 article titled, Othellos Shadow, argued that the Shakespearean work presented a case for abolition of enslaved Africans.

As a widely acclaimed novel highlighting class disparities in 1920s New York, The Great Gatsby transformed the American literary cannon.

William Carlos Williams poem, The Red Wheelbarrow, invites the reader to reconsider the foundations of daily life.

Broadcasted on American television during the 1990s, The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air managed to effectively refute a static representation of blackness in media.
